replyContent: Hi thanks for the comments. Please try the latest update. The NOAA IT department recently changed their download authentication method and it broke the downloads in the app. It should work with the latest version. Thanks for your support!

I don't have a boat. But I do live in a house on the boardwalk in Long Beach, NY. Since I live along the east coast facing the Atlantic Ocean, I felt it was important to know what is going on over the water. I am in no way an expert, but I feel this app affords me access to marine information about my location, that I would be at a loss to have normally. So therefore I would recommend this app to expert and non-expert alike, for what a good job it does informing me about what I need to know.

Outstanding app! Real time buoy data, nearshore and offshore forcasts, a whole bunch of overlays like radar, wind, tide levels, sea height, cloud, rain, forcast,...and a lot more! It's worth the 2 bucks! I'm on Lake Erie, and she can change very quickly. This app is the best I have seen.

The Buoy Data Tide chart and Flood/Ebb charts need to better show the SPECIFIC times of high/low tides and flood/ebb, respectively. Right now you just have to kind of eyeball it. it would be nice to see the exact times of each. It would also be nice to customize the order of info displayed in the Buoy Data section.

I am a professional Mariner and having the weather at my fingertips is a helpful tool.  Pretty good app, forecast zones would be helpful but the point forecast does pretty much the same thing.  Having the ability to save favorite points or zones would be an improvement.  Also, including currents in addition to tides would be great and I would definitely increase my rating if this made the next upgrade.  Anyone transiting the East River, Hell Gate (or any other area where current velocity means more than height of tide) will appreciate this.  Also the app is not reporting information from buoys that are reporting data( I can look them up directly through NDBC).

The ad or write up in the Google Store is very misleading. It implies that the NOAA marine coastal zone forcasts are available, they are not. It has the basic data bouy set and nothing else. Also, within the app, in help, the "Contact Us" email address is invalid, it returns a no such address notice.  At this point in this apps development, Don't Waste Your Money.
replyContent: If you click the icon at the top right in the title bar it will take you to the point forecast tool for retrieving Marine coastal zone forecasts. We'll fix the email issue ASAP. Hope this helps!
